  "text": "The PromQL query parsing and validation pipeline in prometheus/prometheus consists of the following key components:\n\n## Parser Pipeline\n\n### 1. Parser Interface and Implementation (promql/parser/parse.go)\nThe `Parser` interface defines the parsing methods. The `promQLParser` struct implements this interface with two key methods:\n- `ParseExpr(input string)` - Entry point that parses a PromQL expression string\n- `parseExpr()` - Internal recursive parser that builds the AST\n- `checkAST(node Node)` - Validates the AST including type checking after parsing\nThe parser uses a sync.Pool for efficient resource management and supports configuration options like experimental functions and extended range selectors.\n\n### 2. Lexer/Tokenizer (promql/parser/lex.go)\nThe lexer tokenizes the input query string:\n- `Item` struct represents a token with type, position, and value\n- `ItemType` enumeration defines all token types (operators, aggregators, keywords, literals)\n- The lexer uses a state machine to recognize keywords, identifiers, numbers, durations, strings, and special symbols\n- Position tracking is maintained for error reporting via the posrange package\n\n### 3. AST Node Definitions (promql/parser/ast.go)\nDefines the complete Abstract Syntax Tree node hierarchy:\n- `Node` interface - Base interface for all AST nodes\n- `Expr` interface - Base interface for all expression types with a `Type()` method\n- Expression types include:\n  - `VectorSelector` - Metric name and label matchers (e.g., `up{job=\"prometheus\"}`)\n  - `MatrixSelector` - Range vector with time duration (e.g., `http_requests_total[5m]`)\n  - `BinaryExpr` - Binary operations with left/right operands and optional vector matching\n  - `AggregateExpr` - Aggregation functions (sum, avg, count, etc.) with grouping\n  - `Call` - Function calls to built-in functions\n  - `UnaryExpr` - Unary operations (negation)\n  - `NumberLiteral` - Scalar numbers\n  - `StringLiteral` - String values\n  - `ParenExpr` - Parenthesized expressions\n  - `SubqueryExpr` - Subqueries with time ranges\n  - `StepInvariantExpr` - Internal optimization wrapper\n  - `DurationExpr` - Duration literals and expressions\n\n### 4. Value Type System (promql/parser/value.go)\nDefines the type system for expression validation:\n- `ValueType` string constants: `ValueTypeVector`, `ValueTypeScalar`, `ValueTypeMatrix`, `ValueTypeString`, `ValueTypeNone`\n- `Value` interface for runtime values with type information\n- All Expr types implement `Type()` method returning their result type\n\n### 5. Function Registry (promql/parser/functions.go)\nDefines all supported PromQL functions:\n- `Function` struct with: Name, ArgTypes, Variadic count, ReturnType, Experimental flag\n- `Functions` map providing a registry of 100+ built-in functions (abs, rate, increase, histogram_quantile, etc.)\n- Functions specify their argument types for validation during type checking\n\n### 6. Generated Parser (promql/parser/generated_parser.y and generated_parser.y.go)\n- `generated_parser.y` - YACC grammar file defining PromQL syntax\n- `generated_parser.y.go` - Generated parser code produced by goyacc tool\n- Handles operator precedence, associativity, and grammar rules\n- Generated functions like `parseGenerated(startSymbol)` execute the YACC parser\n\n## Validation and Type Checking\n\n### 7. Feature Registry (promql/parser/features.go)\n- `RegisterFeatures()` method registers available PromQL features\n- Tracks enabled operators, aggregators, and functions\n- Supports experimental features controlled by parser options\n\n### 8. AST Utilities (promql/parser/printer.go, prettier.go)\n- `Tree()` function prints AST structure for debugging\n- Pretty printing and formatting of AST back to string form\n- Proper formatting of expressions with correct precedence\n\n### 9. Position Tracking (promql/parser/posrange/posrange.go)\n- `PositionRange` struct tracks start/end positions in the input string\n- Used for precise error reporting and highlighting\n\n## Query Execution Engine\n\n### 10. Engine Integration (promql/engine.go)\nThe `Engine` struct integrates the parser into the query execution pipeline:\n- Uses the Parser to parse query strings into AST\n- Implements `NewInstantQuery()` and `NewRangeQuery()` to create executable queries\n- Executes compiled query plans against TSDB data\n- Handles timeout, cancellation, and resource management\n- Contains EngineOpts for configuration including the parser instance\n\n### 11. Function Implementations (promql/functions.go)\n- Defines `FunctionCall` type for function implementations\n- Implements 100+ built-in functions matching the registry\n- Functions operate on Vector, Matrix, Scalar values\n- Examples: rate, increase, histogram_quantile, vector arithmetic, aggregation functions\n\n## Pipeline Flow\n\n1. **Input**: User provides PromQL query string\n2. **Tokenization**: Lexer converts string to token stream\n3. **Parsing**: YACC parser builds AST from tokens\n4. **Validation**: `checkAST()` validates types and semantics\n5. **Compilation**: Engine optimizes and prepares execution plan\n6. **Execution**: Engine evaluates the query against time series data\n7. **Output**: Returns query results (Vector, Matrix, Scalar, or String)\n\nAll files work together to provide a complete, type-safe PromQL query processing system with comprehensive error reporting and validation."
}

